# Groove Melody & Riffs composer (locked direction)

Replaced **MIDI Bassline Library** UI with **MELODY & RIFFS** panel. Production bass = **NEW SYNTH** only.

## Do not break

- Green **chord** pipeline: DROP CHORDS, `grooveLabRoll` chord channel, MATCH CHORDS ←
- `grooveLabChordAnchorsFromHits` — harmony source for composer
- Beat Lab NEW SYNTH (`beat-lab-synth2-chord-bass-lock.mdc`)

## Architecture

- `grooveComposerEngine.ts` — `generateGrooveComposerPart(part, harmony, complexity, seed)`
- Parts: `melody` | `riff` | `arp` | `bass` (optional sub, C1–C3 only)
- Register: melody/riff/arp = MIDI **49–59** (`GROOVE_LAB_MELODY_*`), chords **≥60**, sub **24–48**
- Merge via `grooveComposerMergePart` — regen one part without wiping others

## UI

- `GrooveLabComposerPanel` — MELODY, RIFF, ARP, VARIATION, + SUB (optional), MATCH CHORDS ←
- Requires chord columns first (`chordColumnCount > 0`)
- Complexity slider 0..1 persisted `groove-lab-composer-complexity`

## Transport

- `GrooveLabTransportEvent` includes `kind: 'melody'` — uses `melodySoundId` (guitar presets)

## Forbidden

- Re‑centering this panel on 808 pattern templates (`grooveLabBassGrooves` as primary UX)
- Driving chord generation from bass templates
- Modifying Chord Builder as a full InstaComposer clone in v1
